reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not just for pantries! Great book storage.
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a space saving solution for children's books and this over the door solution works perfectly. Easy assembly, nice price point, sturdy, can hold a ton of books of all sizes (see pic for side view). The bedroom door closes with ease and still allows space to open the door completely. The rack doesn't move around, the plastic barrier suction type things help the bottom stay in place but are more buffers than anything. The white rack has a pleasing look next to floating white shelves, in other words it doesn't look so out of place in a room vs pantry. Now the books are visible while saving floor space :) The bottom 2 shelves can be easily reached by a small child. Super happy this worked out so well for our needs, 10/10 would buy again.

reviews.reviewText: I loved the ease in which it went together, the instructions were very clear and concise. We use in in our pantry. Saves us a lot of space.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Is what it is
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble, seems sturdy enough once loaded. I would have liked the baskets to be a bit wider it will only accommodate 2 pasta bags the way I have them now. But otherwise it's worth the money, and I'm thinking of getting another for the other door. Will update after a few months of use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I went through 3 different ones before I found this one. I have a really small pantry door (not that wide) and I was just trying to find one that would fit. This one is great the one draw back is the screws to help tighten at the top are super long and stick out alot once it’s closed. It holds everything I need mostly spices and has room for some more. The black is perfect with my kitchen decor. I would highly recommend this one it’s a good buy and it’s working great.
